"use strict";(self.webpackChunkwoocommerce_ebay_connector=self.webpackChunkwoocommerce_ebay_connector||[]).push([[620],{2885(e,a,t){t.r(a),t.d(a,{comp:()=>l,data:()=>u});var o=t(641);const s=t.p+"assets/img/manage-categories.8674bc4c.webp",r=t.p+"assets/img/parent-category.335ff364.webp",i=t.p+"assets/img/import-all-node.18ad33c7.webp",n=t.p+"assets/img/map-categories-tab.0dd8cd2e.webp",p=t.p+"assets/img/sub-categories.7cd0df56.webp",c=t.p+"assets/img/categories-list.c1fb7b24.webp",g=t.p+"assets/img/condition.80d39c0e.webp",m=t.p+"assets/img/attribute.92161f12.webp",h=t.p+"assets/img/auto-mapping-setting.a4d70453.webp",d={},l=(0,t(6262).A)(d,[["render",function(e,a){return(0,o.uX)(),(0,o.CE)("div",null,[...a[0]||(a[0]=[(0,o.Fv)('<h1 id="category-mapping-–-woocommerce-ebay-connector" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#category-mapping-–-woocommerce-ebay-connector"><span>Category Mapping – WooCommerce eBay Connector</span></a></h1><p>This guide explains how to manage and map eBay categories with WooCommerce categories.</p><hr><h2 id="manage-categories" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#manage-categories"><span>Manage Categories</span></a></h2><p>The admin can import categories so WooCommerce automatically assigns imported products to the mapped category.</p><p>Navigate to <strong>WC eBay Connector → Manage Categories</strong> to see the complete list of imported categories. <img src="'+s+'" alt="screenshots"></p><h3 id="steps-to-import-categories" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#steps-to-import-categories"><span>Steps to Import Categories</span></a></h3><ol><li>Click <strong>Create Primary Categories from eBay</strong> to import the categories to the WooCommerce store.</li><li>Click <strong>Import all Node Category of this category</strong> to create the imported categories in the WooCommerce store. <img src="'+r+'" alt="screenshots"><img src="'+i+'" alt="screenshots"></li></ol><hr><h2 id="map-categories" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#map-categories"><span>Map Categories</span></a></h2><p>After importing categories, map them by clicking on the <strong>Map Categories</strong> tab.</p><p>Under this tab, you will see the <strong>Map eBay Primary Categories</strong> option. <img src="'+n+'" alt="screenshots"></p><h3 id="steps-to-map-categories" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#steps-to-map-categories"><span>Steps to Map Categories</span></a></h3><ol><li>Click <strong>Map eBay Primary Categories</strong>.</li><li>A new page will appear — mapping of only <strong>one category</strong> happens at a time.</li><li>Select the <strong>sub-category</strong> for mapping (parent categories cannot be mapped).</li><li>After mapping, the categories will appear in the list. <img src="'+p+'" alt="screenshots"></li></ol><p><img src="'+c+'" alt="screenshots"></p><blockquote><p><strong>Note:</strong> At the time of mapping, the admin creates the eBay condition &amp; specification as product attributes in WooCommerce.</p></blockquote><hr><h2 id="category-condition" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#category-condition"><span>Category Condition</span></a></h2><p>After mapping a category, the mapped store category&#39;s products will show the field of <strong>eBay category condition</strong> on the add/edit product page. <img src="'+g+'" alt="screenshots"> The conditions provided for the category must be filled in to successfully export products to eBay.</p><hr><h2 id="category-specification" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#category-specification"><span>Category Specification</span></a></h2><p>After mapping a category, the mapped store category&#39;s products will show the <strong>category specification of eBay</strong> as global attributes on the add/edit product page under <strong>Product Data</strong>.</p><p>You can check the eBay category specification-based global categories by navigating to <strong>Products → Attributes</strong> in the WordPress admin panel.</p><p>WooCommerce shows the global attribute using the mapped eBay category name. <img src="'+m+'" alt="screenshots"></p><blockquote><p>All attributes with mapped store category names in the format <strong>Attribute name[mapped category name]</strong> must be provided with values by the admin.</p></blockquote><hr><h2 id="auto-mapping" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#auto-mapping"><span>Auto Mapping</span></a></h2><p>If <strong>Auto Mapping</strong> is enabled in the plugin settings, products imported from eBay will automatically be assigned to the eBay category that was already imported in WooCommerce. <img src="'+h+'" alt="screenshots"></p><p>To enable Auto Mapping:</p><ol><li>Go to <strong>WC eBay Connector → eBay Settings → General Settings</strong></li><li>Enable <strong>Auto Mapping</strong></li></ol><hr>',31)])])}]]),u=JSON.parse('{"path":"/documentation/category-mapping.html","title":"Category Mapping – WooCommerce eBay Connector","lang":"en-US","frontmatter":{},"git":{"updatedTime":1772114569000,"contributors":[{"name":"shakir.hussain","username":"","email":"shakir.hussain421@webkul.in","commits":1},{"name":"aadesh","username":"","email":"aadesh.8209@webkul.in","commits":2}],"changelog":[{"hash":"2d5c39163a248635a79c60d8508c0716b0a11c03","time":1772114569000,"email":"aadesh.8209@webkul.in","author":"aadesh","message":"add export product"},{"hash":"a3379ad1acde7722f52940c853addb733657393e","time":1771942912000,"email":"aadesh.8209@webkul.in","author":"aadesh","message":"update images"},{"hash":"277c5a1bdc13e06551e102ee26c728b6b048e50b","time":1771481506000,"email":"shakir.hussain421@webkul.in","author":"shakir.hussain","message":"updated ebay blog and move to dev"}]},"filePathRelative":"documentation/category-mapping.md"}')}}]);